    "answer_id" : 36998473,
    "question_id" : 18987228,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Change JDK version to 1.8</p>\n\n<ol>\n<li>Language level File -> project Structure -> Modules -> Sources -> Language level -> 8-Lambdas, type annotations etc.\n<a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/THoBc.png\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/THoBc.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></a></li>\n<li><p>Project SDk File -> project Structure -> Project 1.8\n<a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/cBaxF.png\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/cBaxF.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></a></p></li>\n<li><p>Java compiler File -> Settings -> Build, Executions, Deployment -> Compiler -> Java compiler\n<a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/AwUnH.png\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/AwUnH.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></a></p></li>\n</ol>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 91056,
      "reputation" : 126856,
      "user_id" : 250260,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 80,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/ZDHrv.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Jorgesys",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/250260/jorgesys"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 32,
    "last_activity_date" : 1516293841,
    "last_edit_date" : 1516293841,
    "creation_date" : 1485971345,
    "answer_id" : 41986342,
    "question_id" : 18987228,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>I have found out that in recent versions of IntelliJ IDEA requires Java 1.8 but is not configured by default.</p>\n\n<p>We can change the path or configure from <strong><code>Project Settings</code></strong> > <strong><code>Project</code></strong> > <strong><code>Project SDK</code></strong></p>\n\n<p>here we can edit or add the JDK´s path.</p>\n\n<p>(in my case the path is located in <code>C:\\Program Files\\Java\\jdk1.8.0_102</code>)</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/QwSu3.png\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/QwSu3.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/8XfEw.png\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/8XfEw.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 63286,
      "reputation" : 4632,
      "user_id" : 187423,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 83,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/6c6ead360d6847d262f83b40946ba06f?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "barclay",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/187423/barclay"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 11,
    "last_activity_date" : 1530631655,
    "last_edit_date" : 1530631655,
    "creation_date" : 1491255944,
    "answer_id" : 43194854,
    "question_id" : 18987228,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>One other place worth checking: Look in the pom.xml for your project, if you are using Maven compiler plugin, at the source/target config and make sure it is the desired version of Java. I found that I had 1.7 in the following; I changed it to 1.8 and then everything compiled correctly in IntelliJ. </p>\n\n<pre><code>&lt;build&gt;\n&lt;plugins&gt;\n    &lt;plugin&gt;\n        &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.maven.plugins&lt;/groupId&gt;\n        &lt;artifactId&gt;maven-compiler-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;\n        &lt;version&gt;2.3.2&lt;/version&gt;\n        &lt;configuration&gt;\n            &lt;source&gt;1.8&lt;/source&gt;\n            &lt;target&gt;1.8&lt;/target&gt;\n            &lt;encoding&gt;UTF-8&lt;/encoding&gt;\n        &lt;/configuration&gt;\n    &lt;/plugin&gt;\n&lt;/plugins&gt;\n&lt;/build&gt;\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
